Suggested clause (ready to insert)

Illustrative Example and Calculation Conventions. For the avoidance of doubt, any numeric example, demonstration or calculation in this Agreement (including, without limitation, the example “2 + 2 = 4”) is included solely for illustrative and explanatory purposes and is not part of the operative provisions of this Agreement. The parties agree that:

(a) the operative amount or result required by this Agreement shall be determined only by applying the express calculation provisions and defined terms of this Agreement, and not by reliance on any illustrative example;

(b) all arithmetic shall be performed using standard base‑10 arithmetic and the conventional order of operations (parentheses, exponents, multiplication and division, addition and subtraction). Numbers shall be expressed in Arabic numerals; if the same number is expressed in words and numerals, the numerals shall control to the extent of any inconsistency;

(c) monetary amounts are denominated in [insert currency, e.g., “United States dollars (USD)”] unless otherwise specified, and all monetary calculations shall be rounded to two decimal places (nearest cent) using “round half up” (i.e., amounts of 0.005 or greater are rounded up);

(d) no party shall assert that any illustrative example is evidence of an intent to modify or vary the operative provisions of this Agreement, and in the event of any inconsistency between an illustrative example and an express provision of this Agreement, the express provision shall control; and

(e) nothing in this clause limits any party’s right to seek relief for mistakes in calculation expressly provided for elsewhere in this Agreement.

Shorter alternative (if you prefer brevity)

Illustrative Example. Any numeric example in this Agreement (including “2 + 2 = 4”) is provided for illustration only and is not part of the operative terms. The Agreement’s express calculation provisions govern. All arithmetic is standard base‑10 with conventional order of operations; monetary amounts are in [currency] and rounded to two decimal places (round half up); in case of conflict the express provisions prevail.

If you want, I can tailor the currency, rounding convention (e.g., bankers’ rounding), or order‑of‑operations wording to a particular jurisdiction or drafting style.
